explanation: The solution iterates through the bits of the input integer from right to left. It maintains a boolean variable `prevBit` to store the value of the previous bit. If the current bit is the same as the previous bit, it returns `false`. Otherwise, it updates `prevBit` and shifts the integer to the right by one bit. The loop continues until all bits have been checked.

